<bill id="DLM3166910" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ" year.imprint="2010" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
  <billdetail>
    <title>State Sector Management Bill</title>
    <billtype>Government Bill</billtype>
    <explnote id="DLM3166911" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
      <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>General policy statement</heading>
        <para>
          <text>The State Sector Management Bill is an omnibus Bill providing for machinery of government changes.  The purpose of the Bill is to amalgamate a number of existing agencies to achieve gains in terms of financial efficiencies, effectiveness, and future viability of agencies. These objectives are consistent with the Government’s overall direction for the State Services portfolio.  The agencies being amalgamated are the Ministry of Research, Science, and Technology and the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology, which will be amalgamated into a new Ministry of Science and Innovation, and the National Library and Archives New Zealand, which will be amalgamated into the Department of Internal Affairs.</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <text>The State Sector Management Bill—</text>
          <list>
            <item>
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>repeals the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990 and replaces it with legislation that provides for the establishment of boards that will make decisions on the allocation of specified research, science, and technology funding. The Bill also provides for the transfer of staff from the Ministry of Research, Science, and Technology and the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology to the new Ministry of Science and Innovation, and from the National Library of New Zealand Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa and Archives New Zealand (Te Rua Mahara o te Kāwanatanga) to the Department of Internal Affairs:</text>
              </para>
            </item>
            <item>
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>amends the National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Act 2003 to reflect the change of status of the National Library from a Public Service department to being integrated into the Department of Internal Affairs, while preserving the statutory functions of the National Librarian and Chief Librarian of the Alexander Turnbull Library:</text>
              </para>
            </item>
            <item>
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>amends the Public Records Act 2005 to reflect the change of status of Archives New Zealand from a Public Service department to being integrated into the Department of Internal Affairs, while preserving the statutory functions of the Chief Archivist with particular emphasis on those functions that must be exercised independently, without direction from the Minister or the chief executive.</text>
              </para>
            </item>
          </list>
        </para>
        <para>
          <text>It is intended that this Bill be divided into the following 3 separate Bills at the committee of the whole House stage: a Research, Science, and Technology Bill, a National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Amendment Bill, and a Public Records Amendment Bill.</text>
        </para>
      </explnote.group>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>Clause by clause analysis</heading>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 1</emphasis> is the Title clause.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 2</emphasis> is the commencement clause. The Bill comes into force on 1 Febuary 2011.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <explnote.part id="DLM3166912">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1  </label>
          <heading>Provisions relating to research, science, and technology</heading>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 3</emphasis> sets out the purpose of this Part.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 4</emphasis> sets out a number of defined terms. These include definitions of former department (to mean the Ministry of Research, Science, and Technology) and Ministry (to mean the department responsible for the administration of this Part).</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 5</emphasis> defines the term specified RS&amp;T funding.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 6</emphasis> provides that this Part binds the Crown.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166913">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <heading>Allocation of funding</heading>
            <explnote.crosshead>Purposes</explnote.crosshead>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 7</emphasis> sets out the purposes for which specified RS&amp;T funding may be allocated.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <explnote.crosshead>Criteria for assessing RS&amp;T funding</explnote.crosshead>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 8</emphasis> requires the Minister responsible for administration of this Part to set criteria for the assessment of proposals for specified RS&amp;T funding, which are binding on a board established by <emphasis style="italic">clause 10</emphasis>. The Minister is not authorised to give a direction in respect of the production of outputs relating to research, science, or technology, or related activities, by a particular person or to direct a board to allocate funds to or for the benefit of a particular person.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <explnote.crosshead>Decision making on specified RS&amp;T funding</explnote.crosshead>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 9</emphasis> requires the chief executive to refer proposals for allocation of specified RS&amp;T funding to the appropriate board established under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10</emphasis>.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 10</emphasis> requires the Minister to establish 1 or more boards and to appoint their members and chairpersons. Before establishing a board, the Minister is required to consult with other interested Ministers. The Minister may specify that a board is to make funding decisions in relation to 1 or more areas of research, science, or technology. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 10(4)</emphasis> states that the functions of a board are (under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10(4)(a)</emphasis>) to make funding decisions on proposals for specified RS&amp;T funding in relation to its areas of research, science, or technology (if any) specified by the Minister and (under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10(4)(b)</emphasis>), with the prior approval of the Minister, to make funding decisions on other RS&amp;T funding proposals referred to it by any other Minister of the Crown or the administrative head of any of the State services. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 10(5)</emphasis> provides that, in carrying out its functions under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10(4)(a)</emphasis>, a board must act in accordance with the purposes in <emphasis style="italic">clause 7</emphasis> and the criteria set by the Minister under <emphasis style="italic">clause 8</emphasis>, and based on information presented to the Board by the chief executive of the Ministry. It also must make funding decisions in an independent, fair, and transparent manner. In carrying out its functions under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10(4)(b)</emphasis>, a board must act in accordance with criteria set by the referring Minister or the head of the referring State services agency (a <emphasis style="bold">referring chief executive</emphasis>), on information provided by the referring Minister or referring chief executive, and in an independent, fair, and transparent matter. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 10(6)</emphasis> requires a board to record its funding decisions in writing and provide them to the chief executive of the Ministry or, as appropriate, the referring Minister or referring chief executive, to give them effect. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 10(7)</emphasis> requires the Ministry to provide administrative support to enable boards to carry out their functions. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 10(8)</emphasis> applies the provisions of <emphasis style="italic">Schedule 1</emphasis> to boards, members, and chairpersons.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 11</emphasis> empowers a board to reconsider any funding decision it has made on referral by the chief executive of the Ministry or, as appropriate, the referring Minister or referring chief executive. On referral, the board may, after taking account of the reasons for the referral, confirm, vary, or revoke the decision, and, if it revokes the decision, the board may make a new funding decision in relation to the RS&amp;T funding that was the subject of the revoked decision. In reconsidering a funding decision, the board must act in accordance with the same provisions as applied to the original decision.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 12</emphasis> empowers a board, with the approval of the Minister, to delegate its functions under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10(4)</emphasis> or powers under <emphasis style="italic">clause 11</emphasis> to the chief executive of the Ministry or a person approved by the Minister who is not any of the State services or an employee in the State services. <emphasis style="italic">Subclause (2)</emphasis> provides that if functions or powers are delegated to the chief executive, the chief executive is not responsible to the Minister for their exercise or performance and the chief executive is required to act independently. The chief executive may also delegate those functions or powers to employees or officers in the Ministry. A person acting under a delegation is bound by the same provisions as apply to the board, and the board is responsible for the performance or exercise of functions or powers under a delegation by any person.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
          </explnote.subpart>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166914">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <heading>Abolition of Foundation and transfer of assets, liabilities, functions, and staff from Foundation, and functions and staff from former department, to Ministry</heading>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 13</emphasis> abolishes the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology on the commencement of this Part, and provides that the members of the Foundation vacate office on that commencement and are not entitled to any compensation or other benefit for loss of office.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 14</emphasis> repeals the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 15</emphasis> transfers the functions of the Ministry of Research, Science, and Technology (the <emphasis style="bold">former department</emphasis>) and Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology (the <emphasis style="bold">Foundation</emphasis>), and their respective chief executives, to the new Ministry of Science and Innovation (the <emphasis style="bold">Ministry</emphasis>) and its chief executive. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 15(2)</emphasis> makes it clear that functions no longer required to be performed as a result of repeal of the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990 are not transferred.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 16</emphasis> vests assets and liabilities of the Foundation, including contracts and other matters, in the Crown acting through the Ministry.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 17</emphasis> transfers employees of the Foundation to the Ministry on the commencement of this Part on the same terms and conditions of employment, and provides that an employee is not entitled to receive any payment or other benefit on the ground that his or her position in the Foundation has ceased to exist.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 18</emphasis> transfers employees of the former department to the Ministry on the commencement of this Part on the same terms and conditions of employment, and provides that an employee is not entitled to receive any payment or other benefit on the ground that his or her position in the former department has ceased to exist. To avoid doubt, <emphasis style="italic">subclause (3)</emphasis> specifies that existing collective contracts continue in force.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 19</emphasis> maintains the terms and conditions of employment of employees transferred under <emphasis style="italic">clause 17 or 18</emphasis> until they are varied by agreement with the Ministry or the employee concerned accepts a subsequent appointment with the Ministry. For the purposes of every enactment, law, determination, contract, and agreement relating to employment of a transferred employee, the employee's employment agreement is treated as unbroken and any previous period of service with or recognised by the Foundation or former department is treated as employment with the Ministry. The employment of a transferred employee is not new employment for the purposes of the KiwiSaver Act 2006 and the employee is not a new employee for the purposes of the Employment Relations Act 2000.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 20</emphasis>  provides that the enactments specified in <emphasis style="italic">Schedule 2</emphasis> are amended in the manner specified in that schedule.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
          </explnote.subpart>
        </explnote.part>
        <explnote.part id="DLM3166915">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2  </label>
          <heading>Amendments to National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Act 2003</heading>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 21</emphasis> provides that this Part amends the National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Act 2003 (the <emphasis style="bold">2003 Act</emphasis>).</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166916">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <heading>Amendments to principal Act</heading>
          </explnote.subpart>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 22</emphasis> amends section 3 of the 2003 Act by substituting a <emphasis style="italic">new paragraph (c)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New paragraph (c)</emphasis> omits the references to the employment status of the National Librarian and the Chief Librarian, both now being employees of the Department of Internal Affairs (the <emphasis style="bold">department</emphasis>) (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> the amendments to sections 8 (<emphasis style="italic">clause 24</emphasis>) and 13 (<emphasis style="italic">clause 28</emphasis>).</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 23</emphasis> amends section 4 of the 2003 Act. The definition of Minister is substituted with the current definition of that term, and the definition of National Library is amended to omit the reference to the National Library being a department. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 23(3)</emphasis> amends section 4 by inserting definitions of chief executive and department.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 24</emphasis> amends section 8 of the 2003 Act by repealing subsections (2) and (3) and substituting a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (2)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (2)</emphasis> provides that the National Librarian is the person for the time being appointed to that office by the chief executive of the department (the <emphasis style="bold">chief executive</emphasis>) under the State Sector Act 1988 (the <emphasis style="bold">1988 Act</emphasis>), and will be an employee in the department. Under the existing section 8(2), the National Librarian is chief executive of the National Library. The existing section 8(3) provided for the continuation of the person who was the National Librarian on the commencement of the 2003 Act. Section 8(3) is no longer required because the purpose of that subsection has now been served. The existing subsections (2) and (3) are therefore no longer appropriate.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 25</emphasis> amends section 9 of the 2003 Act by inserting a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (1AA)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (1AA)</emphasis> provides the National Librarian with the powers necessary to carry out the functions, responsibilities, and duties imposed on the National Librarian under the 2003 Act. Under the existing law, the National Librarian, as the chief executive of the National Library, derived this power from section 34(2) of the 1988 Act. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 25</emphasis> also repeals subsections (2)(b) and (3) and substitutes a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (3)</emphasis>. As the Alexander Turnbull Library will become part of the department, the department will be responsible for the matters specified in the existing subsection (2)(b) (those matters are now dealt with in <emphasis style="italic">new section 11(2A)</emphasis>, which is inserted by <emphasis style="italic">clause 27(1)</emphasis>). <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (3)</emphasis> reflects the new status of the National Library as part of the department. As part of the department, the National Library no longer owns any documents, so the previous requirement that the National Librarian must not transfer ownership of such documents is no longer appropriate.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 26</emphasis> inserts a <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New section 9A</emphasis> enables the National Librarian to delegate all or any of the National Librarian's functions, duties, and powers under the 2003 Act to an employee in the department. However, the power to delegate to the Chief Librarian is limited by section 13(3) and <emphasis style="italic">new section 14</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New section 9A</emphasis> provides a power of delegation in similar terms to the power provided for in section 41(1) of the 1988 Act, which will no longer be available to the National Librarian, as the National Librarian will cease to be a chief executive.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 27</emphasis> amends section 11 of the 2003 Act by inserting a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (2A)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (2A)</emphasis> replaces the requirement in the existing section 9(2)(b) (as repealed by <emphasis style="italic">clause 25</emphasis>) that the National Librarian provide specified resources for the Alexander Turnbull Library. <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (2A)</emphasis> requires the chief executive, in consultation with the National Librarian, to provide such resources.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 28</emphasis> amends section 13 of the 2003 Act. Section 13(2) is amended to require the chief executive to appoint the Chief Librarian on the recommendation of the National Librarian. Under the existing section 13(2), the National Librarian is responsible for the appointment. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 28</emphasis> also amends section 13(3)(b) to replace the reference to the National Librarian with a reference to the chief executive. The National Librarian continues to have a role under section 13(3)(b), because the chief executive, in forming an opinion for the purposes of that provision, is required to consult with the National Librarian. Section 13(3)(b) is further amended to clarify that the powers delegated to the Chief Librarian are those delegated under <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis> (as inserted by <emphasis style="italic">clause 26</emphasis>). Section 13(4) is replaced with a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (4)</emphasis>, which enables the current Chief Librarian to continue in that office as an employee of the department when this Bill is passed.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 29</emphasis> repeals and substitutes section 14 of the 2003 Act. <emphasis style="italic">New section 14</emphasis> repeats the existing section 14, but replaces the reference to section 41 of the 1988 Act with a reference to <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis> (as inserted by <emphasis style="italic">clause 26</emphasis>).</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 30</emphasis> amends section 15(1) and (2)(f) of the 2003 Act by inserting references to <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis>. This reflects the fact that delegation will occur under <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis>, rather than under section 41 of the 1988 Act.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 31</emphasis> amends section 19(1) and (2)(a) of the 2003 Act by inserting references to <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis>. This reflects the fact that delegation will occur under <emphasis style="italic">new section 9A</emphasis>, rather than under section 41 of the 1988 Act.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 32</emphasis> amends section 21(2) of the 2003 Act by replacing a reference to the National Library with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that the department, rather than the National Library, will be responsible for providing the administrative services referred to in section 21. Section 21 provides for administrative services for the Guardians Kaitiaki of the Alexander Turnbull Library, which was established under section 16.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 33</emphasis> amends section 28 of the 2003 Act by replacing a reference to the National Library with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that the department, rather than the National Library, will be responsible for providing the administrative services referred to in section 28. Section 28 provides for administrative services for the Library and Information Advisory Commission Ngā Kaiwhakamārama i ngā Kohikohinga Kōrero, which was established under section 22.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 34</emphasis> repeals section 34(2) of the 2003 Act and substitutes a <emphasis style="italic">new section 34(2)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New section 34(2)</emphasis> largely restates the existing section 34(2), but reflects the fact that, as the National Library will no longer be a department and the National Librarian no longer a chief executive, the employees, contractors, and agents referred to in that subsection are those appointed by or retained by the chief executive.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166917">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <heading>Transfer of employees of National Library and other related matters</heading>
          </explnote.subpart>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 35</emphasis> applies sections 30E, 30F, and 30G of the 1988 Act to persons who were, immediately before the commencement of <emphasis style="italic">Part 2 </emphasis>of this Bill, employees in the National Library. Those sections apply as if they had been declared to apply by Order in Council under section 30C of the 1988 Act.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 36</emphasis> provides that the enactments specified in <emphasis style="italic">Schedule 3</emphasis> are amended in the manner specified in that schedule.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
        </explnote.part>
        <explnote.part id="DLM3166918">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3  </label>
          <heading>Amendments to Public Records Act 2005</heading>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 37</emphasis> provides that this Part amends the Public Records Act 2005 (the <emphasis style="bold">2005 Act</emphasis>).</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166919">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <heading>Amendments to principal Act</heading>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 38</emphasis> amends section 4 of the 2005 Act. The definition of Archives New Zealand is substituted to reflect the fact that Archives New Zealand will be part of the department, and the definition of Minister is substituted to provide the current definition of that term. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 38</emphasis> also inserts definitions of chief executive and department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 39</emphasis> amends section 9 of the 2005 Act by repealing section 9(2). Section 9(2) continues Archives New Zealand as a department of State and, because Archives New Zealand will become part of the department, that subsection is no longer required.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 40</emphasis> amends section 10 of the 2005 Act by repealing subsections (2) and (3) and substituting a <emphasis style="italic">new subsection (2)</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New subsection (2)</emphasis> provides that the Chief Archivist is the person appointed to that office by the chief executive under the 1988 Act, and so will be an employee in the department. Under the existing section 10(2), the Chief Archivist is chief executive of Archives New Zealand. The existing section 10(3) made provision for the continuation in office of the person who was Chief Archivist on the commencement of the 2005 Act. Section 10(3) is no longer required, as the purpose of that subsection has now been served. The existing subsections (2) and (3) are therefore no longer appropriate.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 41</emphasis> repeals section 12 of the 2005 Act and substitutes a <emphasis style="italic">new section 12</emphasis>. <emphasis style="italic">New section 12</emphasis> provides that the Chief Archivist, in relation to the performance of specified functions and duties and the exercise of specified powers, must act independently and is not subject to direction from either the Minister or the chief executive. The existing section 12 provides that the Chief Archivist must act independently, and is not subject to the direction of the Minister, in relation to the disposal of public records under section 20(1).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 42</emphasis> amends section 13(1) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that an employee referred to in section 13(1) will, if this Bill is passed, no longer be an employee of Archives New Zealand and will instead be an employee in the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 43</emphasis> amends section 15(1)(a)(v) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the recordkeeping practices of the Chief Archivist. This amendment reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand, as part of the department, will no longer be subject to audits under section 34. Instead, the audit will cover the recordkeeping practices of the Chief Archivist. <emphasis style="italic">Clause 51</emphasis> makes a corresponding amendment to section 34 (which currently deals with audits of Archives New Zealand).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 44</emphasis> amends section 16(2) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that the department, rather than Archives New Zealand, will be responsible for providing the administrative services referred to in section 16. Section 16 provides for administrative services for the Archives Council, which was established under section 14.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 45</emphasis> amends section 19(2) of the 2005 Act by omitting a reference to Archives New Zealand. The effect of this amendment will be that the Chief Archivist must still make the registers (that are referred to in section 19(1)) available for public inspection, but not necessarily at Archives New Zealand.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 46</emphasis> amends section 20(3) and (4) of the 2005 Act. Section 20(3) is amended by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the Chief Archivist in relation to his or her functions, duties, and powers under the 2005 Act. This reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer be a department, so will be unable to create or receive documents. The amendment to section 20(4) makes that subsection consistent with the amended section 20(3).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 47</emphasis> amends section 21 of the 2005 Act by substituting <emphasis style="italic">new subsections (1)(a) and (2)(b)(i)</emphasis>. These amendments reflect the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, and controlled by the Chief Archivist, will in future be possessed by the department but continue to be controlled by the Chief Archivist.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 48</emphasis> amends section 22(3)(a) and (5)(b) of the 2005 Act. The amendment to section 22(3)(a) reflects the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, and controlled by the Chief Archivist will in future be possessed by the department but continue to be controlled by the Chief Archivist. The amendment to section 22(5)(b) reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer be able to make the payments referred to in that paragraph, as it will no longer be a department. The amended paragraph will require the department to be responsible for such payments.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 49</emphasis> amends section 25(1)(f) of the 2005 Act to replace a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer have employees and that the employee referred to in section 25(1)(f) will be an employee in the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 50</emphasis> amends section 26(2)(d) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department. The amendment also makes it clear that the department is not an approved repository.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 51</emphasis> amends the heading to section 34 and section 34(1) of the 2005 Act by replacing references to Archives New Zealand with references to the recordkeeping practices of the Chief Archivist. These amendments reflect the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer be a department and that audits under section 34 will in future be carried out in relation to the recordkeeping practices of the Chief Archivist.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 52</emphasis> amends section 38(4)(a) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 53</emphasis> amends section 44(6) of the 2005 Act by removing the reference to Archives New Zealand. This amendment reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer be a department and cannot, therefore, be subject to the requirements of the existing section 44(6). Section 44(6) currently requires both Archives New Zealand, as a department, and the Chief Archivist to comply with conditions of access imposed under section 44(3)(b).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 54</emphasis> amends section 47 of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 55</emphasis> amends section 58 of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that documents previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 56</emphasis> amends section 60(2) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that Archives New Zealand will no longer be a department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 57</emphasis> amends section 64(2)(b) of the 2005 Act by replacing a reference to Archives New Zealand with a reference to the department. This amendment reflects the fact that a public archive previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 58</emphasis> amends section 65(2)(g) and (h) of the Act by replacing references to Archives New Zealand with references to the department. These amendments reflect the fact that public archives previously possessed by Archives New Zealand, as a department, will in future be possessed by the department.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
          </explnote.subpart>
          <explnote.subpart id="DLM3166920">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <heading>Transfer of employees of Archives New Zealand and other related matters</heading>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 59</emphasis> applies sections 30E, 30F, and 30G of the 1988 Act to persons who were, immediately before the commencement of <emphasis style="italic">Part 3</emphasis> of this Bill, employees in Archives New Zealand. Those sections apply as if they had been declared to apply by Order in Council under section 30C of the 1988 Act.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 60</emphasis> provides that the enactments specified in <emphasis style="italic">Schedule 4</emphasis> are amended in the manner specified in that schedule.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <explnote.crosshead>
              <emphasis style="roman">
                <emphasis style="bold">Schedules</emphasis>
              </emphasis>
            </explnote.crosshead>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Schedule 1</emphasis> sets out provisions, many of which are based on provisions in the Crown Entities Act 2004, relating to boards established under <emphasis style="italic">clause 10</emphasis> of the Bill, chairpersons of boards, and members of boards.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 1</emphasis> sets out the method of appointing or reappointing a member of a board and a chairperson of a board by the Minister.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 2</emphasis> provides that the number of members of a board is in the Minister's discretion, and sets the criteria for appointment of members.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 3</emphasis> provides that the acts of members and chairpersons of boards are valid even though there was a defect in their appointments or the occasion for their acting had not arisen or had ended.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 4</emphasis> provides that the appointments of members and chairpersons are not invalid only because of a defect in their appointments. This does not apply to a defect in a member's qualifications for appointment.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 5</emphasis> sets the term of office for members at a maximum of 3 years, and allows reappointment. It also provides that a member continues in office after the expiry of his or her term of office until the member is reappointed, a successor is appointed, or the member is informed by the Minister that he or she will not be reappointed and no successor will be appointed.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 6</emphasis> gives the Minister discretion to remove a member from office at any time by notice to the member (with a copy to the board).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 7</emphasis> allows members to resign from office.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 8</emphasis> provides that a chairperson of a board holds office until resignation, removal by the Minister, or ceasing to hold office as a member.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 9</emphasis> allows a chairperson to resign that office without resigning as a member.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 10</emphasis> authorises the Minister to remove a chairperson from office with or without also removing him or her as a member of a board.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 11</emphasis> provides that a member or chairperson is not entitled to any payment or other benefit for loss of office for any reason.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 12</emphasis> allows a board to regulate its own procedure.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 13</emphasis> sets out provisions relating to meetings of the board, including how a meeting is called, who is to preside, the quorum requirements, the voting rights of members, the chairperson's casting vote, and how resolutions are passed.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 14</emphasis> sets out the method of holding meetings, which can include audio, audio and visual, or electronic communication.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 15</emphasis> enables a board to pass a resolution in writing signed or assented to by all members without holding a meeting.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 16</emphasis> authorises a board to appoint 1 or more of its members as a subcommittee under the control of the board, and to delegate its functions and powers to a subcommittee.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 17</emphasis> sets out the collective duties of a board and its members, and the consequences of not complying with them.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clauses 18 to 23</emphasis> set out the individual duties of members as—</text>
                <list>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty to comply with <emphasis style="italic">clause 10 and Schedule 1</emphasis> of the Bill (<emphasis style="italic">clause 18</emphasis>):</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty to act with honesty and integrity (<emphasis style="italic">clause 19</emphasis>):</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty to act in good faith (<emphasis style="italic">clause 20</emphasis>):</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty to act with reasonable care, diligence, and skill (<emphasis style="italic">clause 21</emphasis>):</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty not to disclose information (<emphasis style="italic">clause 22</emphasis>):</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                    <para>
                      <text>the duty to disclose conflicts of interest (<emphasis style="italic">clause 23</emphasis>).</text>
                    </para>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 24</emphasis> provides for members' accountability for individual duties.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 25</emphasis> sets out a member's immunity from civil liability in respect of an excluded act or omission (as defined in <emphasis style="italic">clause 28</emphasis>).</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 26</emphasis> authorises the chief executive of the Ministry to effect insurance cover for a member in relation to his or her acts or omissions, except acts done or omissions made in bad faith or acts and omissions that do not relate to the performance of the board's functions.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 27</emphasis> requires a member who is insured by the chief executive to repay any cost in excess of that which could have been provided or effected under the Bill, and provides for recovery of the amount as a debt.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 28</emphasis> defines certain terms for the purpose of <emphasis style="italic">clauses 25 to 27</emphasis>.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 29</emphasis> declares a board to be a statutory Board for the purposes of the Fees and Travelling Allowances Act 1951, and authorises the Minister to direct that board members may be paid remuneration and travelling allowances and expenses in accordance with that Act.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Schedule 2</emphasis> makes consequential amendments to the specified enactments. These amendments are a consequence of changes to be made by <emphasis style="italic">Part 1</emphasis> of this Bill.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Schedule 3</emphasis> makes consequential amendments to the specified enactments. These amendments are a consequence of the amendments made by <emphasis style="italic">Part 2</emphasis> of this Bill.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
            <clause.desc>
              <para>
                <text><emphasis style="italic">Schedule 4</emphasis> makes consequential amendments to the specified enactments. These amendments are a consequence of the amendments made by <emphasis style="italic">Part 3</emphasis> of this Bill.</text>
              </para>
            </clause.desc>
          </explnote.subpart>
        </explnote.part>
      </explnote.group>
    </explnote>
  </billdetail>
  <cover id="DLM3166921">
    <member>Hon Tony Ryall</member>
    <title>State Sector Management Bill</title>
    <billtype>Government Bill</billtype>
  </cover>
  <contents>
    <heading>Contents</heading>
    <toc/>
  </contents>
  <front id="DLM3166922">
    <enactment>The Parliament of New Zealand enacts as follows:</enactment>
  </front>
  <body id="DLM3166923" prov-type="clause">
    <prov id="DLM3166924" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
      <heading>Title</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>This Act is the State Sector Management Act <changeable>2010</changeable>.</text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <prov id="DLM3166925" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
      <heading>Commencement</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>This Act comes into force on 1 February 2011.</text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <part id="DLM3166926" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
      <heading>Provisions relating to research, science, and technology</heading>
      <prov id="DLM3166927" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
        <heading>Purpose</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>The purpose of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable> is—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>to establish boards to make independent funding decisions in respect of the allocation of specified funds appropriated for the purposes of research, science, technology, or related activities:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>to repeal the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para>
                  <text>to provide for the transfer of functions, employees, assets, and liabilities from the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology to a new department of State:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                <para>
                  <text>to provide for the transfer of functions and employees from the former department to a new department of State:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                <para>
                  <text>to provide for savings in relation to contracts with the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology, consequential amendments, and other savings and transitional matters.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM3166928" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
        <heading>Interpretation</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>In <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, unless the context otherwise requires,—</text>
              <def-para id="DLM3166929">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166930">board</def-term> means a board established under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(1)</citation></changeable></text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166931">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166932">chief executive</def-term> means the chief executive of the Ministry</text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166933">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166934">employee</def-term> has the same meaning as in section 2 of the State Sector Act 1988</text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166935">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166936">former department</def-term> means the Ministry of Research, Science, and Technology </text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166937">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166938">Foundation</def-term> means the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology established by section 4 of the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990</text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166939">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166940">member</def-term>,—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>in relation to a board established under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(1)</citation></changeable>, means a member of that board; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>for the purposes of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 13</citation></changeable>, means a member of the Foundation</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166941">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166942">Minister</def-term> means the Minister of the Crown who, under the authority of any warrant or with the authority of the Prime Minister, is for the time being responsible for the administration of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable></text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166943">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166944">Ministry</def-term> means the department that is, with the authority of the Prime Minister, for the time being responsible for administration of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable></text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166945">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166946">outputs </def-term> means goods or services; and includes knowledge and information </text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166947">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166948">RS&amp;T funding</def-term> means the expenses authorised by non-departmental appropriations within the meaning of Part 1 of the Public Finance Act 1989 for research, science, or technology, or related activities</text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166949">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166950">specified RS&amp;T funding</def-term> has the meaning set out in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 5</citation></changeable></text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
              <def-para id="DLM3166951">
                <para>
                  <text><def-term id="DLM3166952">State services</def-term> has the same meaning as it has in section 2 of the State Sector Act 1988.</text>
                </para>
              </def-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM3166953" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
        <heading>Meaning of specified RS&amp;T funding</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>In <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, <def-term id="DLM3166954">specified RS&amp;T funding</def-term>—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>means RS&amp;T funding in a vote administered by the Ministry in respect of which a decision on rationing a limited amount of that funding is required to be made, in accordance with criteria published under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 8(1)</citation></changeable>,—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>between eligible proposals, as to which should receive an allocation; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>in response to an individual proposal, as to the amount (if any) to be allocated; but</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>does not include RS&amp;T funding in a vote administered by the Ministry that is subject to a separate decision-making process.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>For the purpose of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)(b)</citation></changeable>, the Minister must, by notice published in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>, identify any RS&amp;T funding in a vote administered by the Ministry that is subject to a separate decision-making process.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM3166955" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
        <heading>Part binds the Crown</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">This Part</citation></changeable> binds the Crown.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <subpart id="DLM3166956" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
        <heading>Allocation of funding</heading>
        <crosshead id="DLM3166957" toc="yes">Purposes</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM3166958" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">7</label>
          <heading>Purposes for which specified RS&amp;T funding may be allocated</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Specified RS&amp;T funding may be allocated for research, science, or technology, or related activities, for the benefit of New Zealand.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The activities referred to in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> include (but are not limited to) any activity that—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is likely to increase knowledge or understanding of the physical, biological, or social environment; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is likely to contribute to New Zealand’s economic growth; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is likely to develop, maintain, or increase skills or scientific or technological expertise that is of particular importance to New Zealand; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is unlikely to be funded, or adequately funded, from non-governmental sources; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>facilitates RS&amp;T; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">f</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>promotes or facilitates the application of RS&amp;T; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">g</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>promotes or facilitates the application of technological developments.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM3166959" toc="yes">Criteria for assessing RS&amp;T funding</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM3166960" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">8</label>
          <heading>Minister to set, and boards to adhere to, criteria</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Minister must from time to time, by notice given to each board and published in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>, set criteria for the assessment of proposals for specified RS&amp;T funding.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>A board must carry out its functions under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(4)(a)</citation></changeable> in accordance with the criteria set under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Nothing in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> authorises the Minister to— </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>give a direction in respect of the production, by a particular person, of outputs relating to research, science, or technology, or related activities; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>direct a board to allocate funds to or for the benefit of a particular person.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM3166961" toc="yes">Decision making on specified RS&amp;T funding</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM3166962" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">9</label>
          <heading>Ministry to refer proposals to boards</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>On any occasion when decisions on the allocation of specified RS&amp;T funding are to be made, the chief executive must refer the proposals concerned to the appropriate board to make funding decisions in accordance with <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(4)(a) and (5)</citation></changeable>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166963" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">10</label>
          <heading>Establishment, functions, and duties of boards</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Minister must—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>establish, by notice published in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>, 1 or more boards; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>appoint members of those boards; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>appoint a member of each board as the chairperson of that board.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Before establishing a board, the Minister must consult with any other Minister of the Crown whose area of responsibility, in the Minister's opinion, includes an interest in the allocation of specified RS&amp;T funding. </text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Minister may specify that a board is to make funding decisions on proposals for specified RS&amp;T funding in relation to 1 or more areas of research, science, or technology, or related activities, specified in—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the notice establishing the board under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)(a)</citation></changeable>; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice given to the board  for the purpose and published in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The functions of a board established under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)(a)</citation></changeable> are,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in relation to its areas of research, science, or technology, or related activities (if any) specified under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (3)</citation></changeable>, to make funding decisions on proposals for specified RS&amp;T funding referred to it by the chief executive; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>with the prior approval of the Minister, to make decisions on proposals for allocation of RS&amp;T funding that are referred to it—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>by any other Minister of the Crown (a <def-term id="DLM3166964">referring Minister</def-term>); or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>by the administrative head (however called) of any of the State services (a <def-term id="DLM3166965">referring chief executive</def-term>).</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>In performing its functions, a board must act,— </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in relation to its functions under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (4)(a)</citation></changeable>, in accordance with— </text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the purposes in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 7</citation></changeable>; and </text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 8(2)</citation></changeable>; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in relation to its functions under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (4)(b)</citation></changeable>, in accordance with criteria specified by the referring Minister or, as the case requires, the referring chief executive; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>on information presented to the board by the chief executive or, as the case requires, by the referring Minister or referring chief executive; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in an independent, fair, and transparent manner.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>For the purpose of giving effect to the decision, a board must record any funding decision it makes in the performance of its functions in writing and provide that decision to the chief executive or, as the case requires, the referring Minister or referring chief executive.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">7</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Ministry must supply all secretarial and administrative services required to enable a board to carry out its functions.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">8</label>
              <para>
                <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">Schedule 1</citation></changeable> applies to boards and to the members and chairpersons of those boards.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166966" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">11</label>
          <heading>Board may reconsider funding decisions</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A board may, on referral in writing by the chief executive or, as the case requires, a referring Minister or a referring chief executive setting out the reasons for the referral, reconsider any funding decision it has made in the performance of its functions, and, following that reconsideration,— </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>may confirm, vary, or revoke the decision; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if it revokes the decision, may make a new funding decision or decisions in relation to the RS&amp;T funding that was the subject of the revoked decision.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In reconsidering a funding decision, the board must—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>take account of the reasons for the referral; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>act in accordance with—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(5)(a)</citation></changeable> or, as appropriate, <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(5)(b)</citation></changeable>; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(5)(c) and (d)</citation></changeable>.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">Section 10(6)</citation></changeable> applies to any decision of the board under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> as if it were a funding decision.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166967" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">12</label>
          <heading>Board may delegate functions</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>With the approval and within any limits set by the Minister, a board may, either generally or particularly and by resolution, delegate its functions under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(4)</citation></changeable> or powers under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 11</citation></changeable> to—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the chief executive; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any other person (not being an employee in the State services) approved by the Minister.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>If functions or powers are delegated to the chief executive under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable>,— </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the chief executive is not responsible to the Minister for the performance or exercise of those functions or powers but must act independently; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the chief executive may delegate those functions or powers to employees or holders of specified offices in the Ministry under <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 41 of the State Sector Act 1988</citation>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person to whom functions or powers are delegated under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1) or (2)(b)</citation></changeable> must perform or exercise them in accordance with <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 10(5) and (6)</citation></changeable> or, as the case requires, <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 11</citation></changeable>, and those provisions apply with all necessary modifications as if references to a board were references to that person.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>No delegation under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1) or (2)(b)</citation></changeable> affects the responsibility of the board for the actions of any person acting under the delegation.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
      <subpart id="DLM3166968" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
        <heading>Abolition of Foundation and transfer of assets, liabilities, functions, and staff from Foundation, and functions and staff from former department, to Ministry</heading>
        <prov id="DLM3166969" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">13</label>
          <heading>Abolition of Foundation</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>On the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, the Foundation is abolished.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every member of the Foundation vacates office on the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable> and is not entitled to any compensation or other benefit in respect of loss of office.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166970" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">14</label>
          <heading>Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990 repealed</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>The Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990 (1990 No 72) is repealed.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166971" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">15</label>
          <heading>Transfer of functions of former department and Foundation to Ministry</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>On the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the functions and responsibilities of the former department and of the Foundation become the functions and responsibilities of the Ministry; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the functions and responsibilities of the chief executives of the former department and of the Foundation become the functions and responsibilities of the chief executive of the Ministry.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>To avoid doubt, nothing in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> applies to functions and responsibilities of the Foundation or its chief executive that no longer require to be performed as a result of the repeal of the Foundation for Research, Science, and Technology Act 1990.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166972" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">16</label>
          <heading>Vesting of assets and liabilities of Foundation</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>On the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>all property belonging to the Foundation vests in the Crown as assets of the Ministry; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>all information held by the Foundation is held by the Ministry; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>all money payable to or by the Foundation becomes payable to or by the Ministry; and </text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>all rights, liabilities, contracts, entitlements, and engagements of the Foundation become the rights, liabilities, contracts, entitlements, and engagements of the Crown acting through the Ministry; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>anything done, or omitted to be done, or that is to be done by, or in relation to, the Foundation must be treated as having been done, or having been omitted to be done, or to be done by, or in relation to, the Ministry; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">f</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>proceedings commenced, continued, or enforced by or against the Foundation must instead be commenced, continued, or enforced by or against the Crown in respect of the Ministry without amendment to the proceedings; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">g</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a matter or thing that would have, but for this section, been completed by the Foundation, must be completed by the Ministry. </text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>To avoid doubt, the dissolution of the Foundation does not, of itself, affect any of the following matters: </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any decision made, or anything done or omitted to be done, by the Foundation in relation to the performance of the Foundation's functions and duties or the exercise of its powers under any enactment:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any proceedings commenced by or against the Foundation:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any other matter or thing arising out of the Foundation’s performance, or purported performance, of the Foundation’s functions and duties, or the exercise, or purported exercise, of its powers under any enactment.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The dissolution of the Foundation and the transfer of its property, rights, and obligations to the Crown or the Ministry—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is not to be treated as placing a person in breach of, or default under, any contract, or in breach of trust, or in breach of confidence, or as otherwise making the person guilty of a civil wrong; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is not to be treated as entitling a person to—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>terminate or cancel or modify a contract, an agreement, or an arrangement; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>enforce or accelerate the performance of an obligation; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>require the performance of an obligation not otherwise arising for performance; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not release any surety wholly or in part from all or any obligation; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not invalidate or discharge any contract or security.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166973" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">17</label>
          <heading>Transfer of employees of Foundation to Ministry</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every person who was, immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, an employee in the Foundation becomes, on the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, an employee in the Ministry on the same terms and conditions of employment as applied to that employee immediately before that commencement.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>An employee referred to in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> is not entitled to receive any payment or other benefit on the ground that his or her position in the Foundation has ceased to exist.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166974" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">18</label>
          <heading>Transfer of employees of former department to Ministry</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every person who was, immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, an employee in the former department becomes, on the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, an employee in the Ministry on the same terms and conditions of employment as applied to that employee immediately before that commencement.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>An employee referred to in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> is not entitled to receive any payment or other benefit on the ground that his or her position in the former department has ceased to exist.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>To avoid doubt, any collective agreement that was in force immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable> continues in force, and the following persons are bound by, and entitled to enforce, that agreement:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any employee referred to in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation></changeable> who was, immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable>, bound by, and entitled to enforce, that agreement; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the chief executive.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166975" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">19</label>
          <heading>Transferred employees</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The terms and conditions of employment of a transferred employee immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">this Part</citation></changeable> continue to apply in relation to that employee until—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>those terms and conditions are varied by agreement between the transferred employee and the Ministry; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the transferred employee accepts a subsequent appointment with the Ministry.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>For the purposes of every enactment, law, determination, contract, and agreement relating to the employment of a transferred employee,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the employment agreement of that employee is to be treated as unbroken; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the employee’s period of service with the former department or the Foundation, and every other period of service of that employee that is recognised by the former department or the Foundation as continuous service, is to be treated as a period of service with the Ministry.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>To avoid doubt, the employment of a transferred employee by the Ministry does not— </text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>constitute new employment for the purposes of the KiwiSaver Act 2006; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>treat that employee as a new employee for the purposes of the Employment Relations Act 2000.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>In this section, <def-term id="DLM3166976">transferred employee</def-term> means a person who becomes an employee of the Ministry under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 17 or 18</citation></changeable>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166977" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">20</label>
          <heading>Consequential amendments</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>The enactments specified in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">Schedule 2</citation></changeable> are amended in the manner indicated in that schedule.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
    </part>
    <part id="DLM3166978" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
      <heading>Amendments to National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Act 2003</heading>
      <prov id="DLM3166979" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">21</label>
        <heading>Principal Act amended</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">This Part</citation></changeable> amends the National Library of New Zealand (Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa) Act 2003.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <subpart id="DLM3166980" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
        <heading>Amendments to principal Act</heading>
        <prov id="DLM3166981" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">22</label>
          <heading>Purpose</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 3 is amended by repealing paragraph (c) and substituting the following paragraph:</text>
                <amend increment="1" quote="1">
                  <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">c</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>continue the mutually supportive roles of the National Librarian and the Chief Librarian; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </amend>
                <follow-text space-before="no">.</follow-text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166982" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">23</label>
          <heading>Interpretation</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 4 is amended by repealing the definition of <def-term id="DLM3166983">Minister</def-term> and substituting the following definition:</text>
                <amend increment="1" quote="1">
                  <def-para id="DLM3166984" quote="1">
                    <para quote="1">
                      <text><def-term id="DLM3166985">Minister</def-term> means the Minister of the Crown who, under the authority of any warrant or with the authority of the Prime Minister, is for the time being responsible for the administration of this Act</text>
                    </para>
                  </def-para>
                </amend>
                <follow-text space-before="no">.</follow-text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The definition of <def-term id="DLM3166986">National Library</def-term> in section 4 is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">the department of State known as</amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 4 is amended by inserting the following definitions in their appropriate alphabetical order:</text>
                <amend increment="1" quote="1">
                  <def-para id="DLM3166987" quote="1">
                    <para quote="1">
                      <text><def-term id="DLM3166988">chief executive</def-term> means the chief executive of the department</text>
                    </para>
                  </def-para>
                  <def-para id="DLM3166989" quote="1">
                    <para quote="1">
                      <text><def-term id="DLM3166990">department</def-term> means the department of State that, with the authority of the Prime Minister, is for the time being responsible for the administration of this Act</text>
                    </para>
                  </def-para>
                </amend>
                <follow-text space-before="no">.</follow-text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166991" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">24</label>
          <heading>National Librarian</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 8 is amended by repealing subsections (2) and (3) and substituting the following subsection:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">2</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The National Librarian is the person for the time being appointed to that office by the chief executive under the State Sector Act 1988.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166992" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">25</label>
          <heading>Functions and powers of National Librarian</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 9 is amended by inserting the following subsection before subsection (1):</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">1AA</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The National Librarian has all the powers necessary to perform and carry out the functions, responsibilities, and duties imposed on the National Librarian by or under this Act.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 9(2)(b) is repealed.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 9 is amended by repealing subsection (3) and substituting the following subsection:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">3</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The National Librarian must not transfer the custody or use of any documents held by the National Library to any authority or other person, or remove any documents from the collections, without the approval of the Minister.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166993" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">26</label>
          <heading>New section 9A inserted</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>The following section is inserted after section 9:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <prov id="DLM3166994" irdnumbering="no" quote="1" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">9A</label>
                    <heading>Delegations by National Librarian</heading>
                    <prov.body>
                      <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">1</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>The National Librarian may, either generally or particularly, delegate to an employee in the department all or any of the National Librarian's functions, duties, or powers under this Act except the power to delegate.</text>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                      <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">2</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>A delegation—</text>
                          <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">a</label>
                            <para>
                              <text>must be in writing; and</text>
                            </para>
                          </label-para>
                          <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">b</label>
                            <para>
                              <text>may be made subject to any restrictions and conditions the National Librarian thinks fit; and</text>
                            </para>
                          </label-para>
                          <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">c</label>
                            <para>
                              <text>is revocable at any time, in writing; and</text>
                            </para>
                          </label-para>
                          <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">d</label>
                            <para>
                              <text>does not prevent the performance or exercise of a function, duty, or power by the National Librarian.</text>
                            </para>
                          </label-para>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                      <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">3</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>A person to whom any functions, duties, or powers are delegated may perform and exercise them in the same manner and with the same effect as if they had been conferred directly by this Act and not by delegation.</text>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                      <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">4</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>A person who appears to act under a delegation is presumed to be acting in accordance with its terms in the absence of evidence to the contrary.</text>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                      <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">5</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>This section is subject to the limitations specified in sections 13(3) and <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">14</citation></changeable>.</text>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                    </prov.body>
                  </prov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166995" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">27</label>
          <heading>Continuation of Alexander Turnbull Library</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 11 is amended by inserting the following subsection after subsection (2):</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">2A</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The chief executive, in consultation with the National Librarian, must provide—</text>
                      <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">a</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>separate and suitable accommodation in a national library building for the collections of the Alexander Turnbull Library; and</text>
                        </para>
                      </label-para>
                      <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">b</label>
                        <para>
                          <text>for the development of the research collections and the services of the Alexander Turnbull Library, particularly in the fields of New Zealand and Pacific studies and rare books.</text>
                        </para>
                      </label-para>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection 11(3) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">the National Library</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">the department</amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166996" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">28</label>
          <heading>Chief Librarian of Alexander Turnbull Library</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 13(2) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">National Librarian</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">chief executive, on the recommendation of the National Librarian,</amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 13(3)(b) is amended by—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>omitting <amend.in quote="1">the National Library</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">the department</amend.in>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>omitting <amend.in quote="1">the National Librarian</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">the chief executive, in consultation with the National Librarian</amend.in>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>adding <amend.in quote="1">in accordance with <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable></amend.in>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 13 is amended by repealing subsection (4) and substituting the following subsection:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">4</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The person holding office as Chief Librarian immediately before the commencement of <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">Part 2 of the State Sector Management Act 2010</citation></changeable> continues to hold that office on the commencement of that <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">Part</citation></changeable> on the same terms and conditions, to the extent that those terms and conditions are consistent with the Chief Librarian being an employee in the department.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166997" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">29</label>
          <heading>New section 14 substituted</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 14 is repealed and the following section substituted:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <prov id="DLM3166998" irdnumbering="no" quote="1" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">14</label>
                    <heading>Functions, duties, and powers of Chief Librarian</heading>
                    <prov.body>
                      <subprov skeleton="no">
                        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                        <para>
                          <text>The Chief Librarian must perform any functions or duties, and exercise any powers, delegated to him or her under <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable> for preserving, protecting, developing, and making accessible the collections of the Alexander Turnbull Library.</text>
                        </para>
                      </subprov>
                    </prov.body>
                  </prov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3166999" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">30</label>
          <heading>Documents may be made available for public exhibition</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 15(1) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">section 14</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable></amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 15(2)(f) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">section 14</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable></amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3169100" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">31</label>
          <heading>Reports</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 19(1) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">section 14</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable></amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Section 19(2)(a) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">section 14</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 9A</citation></changeable></amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3169101" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">32</label>
          <heading>Administration</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 21(2) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">The National Library</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">The department</amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3169102" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">33</label>
          <heading>Administration</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 28 is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">The National Library</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">The department</amend.in>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM3169103" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">34</label>
          <heading>Use of public documents in National Library</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>Section 34 is amended by repealing subsection (2) and substituting the following subsection:</text>
                <amend quote="1">
                  <subprov skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">2</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>For the purposes of carrying out his or her duties, the National Librarian and any employee, contractor, or agent of the chief executive may possess, copy, store in electronic form (whether offline or online), and use any copy of a deposited document.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </amend>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
      <subpart id="DLM3169104" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" toc="yes" bill.no="193" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
